            Scientists need to master the
            <span class="efrw-phrase"
              data-filter="brevity"
              data-filter-label="Brevity"
              data-found="false"
              data-error-type="Verbose wording"
              data-correction="genre of scientific writing"
              data-explanation="The list of specific genres uses far more words than necessary. A single concise noun phrase conveys the same meaning with greater economy.">genres of scientific abstracts, reports, research articles and dissertations</span>
            to conform to the generic expectations of the community of practice.
            Based on a systematic analysis of the pedagogic literature,
            <span class="efrw-phrase"
              data-filter="clarity"
              data-filter-label="Clarity"
              data-found="false"
              data-error-type="Vague expression"
              data-correction="five categories"
              data-explanation="&lsquo;Some&rsquo; is vague and imprecise. The exact number of categories is known and should be stated to give the reader a clear picture.">some categories</span>
            of errors were identified in scientific research articles namely accuracy, brevity,
            clarity, objectivity, and formality. To gain a more in-depth understanding of the errors,
            <span class="efrw-phrase"
              data-filter="objectivity"
              data-filter-label="Objectivity"
              data-found="false"
              data-error-type="Excessive personalization"
              data-correction="a corpus investigation of scientific articles was conducted"
              data-explanation="Using &lsquo;I&rsquo; focuses attention on the researcher rather than the research process. Passive voice depersonalizes the narrative, meeting the genre expectations of scientific writing.">I conducted a corpus investigation of scientific articles</span>.
            A corpus of 200 draft research articles submitted for internal review at a research
            institute with university status was compiled, annotated, and analyzed. This investigation
